result.execSummary:
The defendant Gary Lee Garrow was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Gary Lee Garrow is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Gary Lee Garrow was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:33 PM Defendant Gary Lee Garrow in court.  Attorney Chris A Gramstrup in court for Gary Lee Garrow.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Victim present in court. Court calls case. State will dismiss Count 1, will plead to Count 2, 90 days imposed and stayed for 1 years, $20 plus costs. 
Court recounts charges and possible penalties. Defendant pleads no contest. Court informs defendant of rights given up by their plea. Attorney stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. Court finds Defendant understands all the rights they are waiving by their plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered. Any remaining charges dismissed.
Victim makes statement. 
Parties agree that this is an appropriate resolution. Attorney Gramstrup indicates 3 days credit.
Defendant makes statements.
Court orders 90 days I&S 1 year, conditions of $20 fine plus costs, DOC programming, 3 days, 3 credit, time served.
